item.title: Test Post
item.description: Hello, my name is Chris Hinds. I’m a biology major at UT Austin, and I’m pre-med. In addition to biology, I enjoy coding from time to time. Here is a little bit of python and R that I have learned! library(reticulate) library(ggplot2) reticulateisfun <- "Biology major at the University of Texas at Austin" one = 1 two = 2 five = 5 ten = 10 one + five * ten ## 51 list=[1,20,290,-1,63,14,613] max(list) ## 613 min(list) ## -1 list[3:6] ## [-1, 63, 14] myname = 'Christopher Mark Hinds' myeid = 'cmh5256' myname + ', ' + myeid ## 'Christopher Mark Hinds, cmh5256' print(myname, "\n", r.
